text: Tipanaea patulella is a moth of the family Crambidae described by Francis Walker in 1863. It is known from Australia, where it is found from Queensland to Tasmania. The wingspan is about 30 mm. Adults are white."Tipanaea patulella Walker, 1863". Australian Caterpillars and their Butterflies and Moths. Retrieved 3 March 2018. The larvae are thought to bore into the stems of Juncus species. ==References== Category:Schoenobiinae
title: Tipanaea patulella
